04/02/2004
WASHINGTON, United States -- Undersecretary of State for Arms Control and International Security John Bolton discussed issues of NATO integration Tuesday (3 February) with visiting Albanian Defence Minister Pandeli Majko.
During the meeting, Majko reiterated his government's commitment to implement reforms necessary for achieving NATO and EU standards.
He added that the Adriatic Charter, drafted in co-operation with the United States, is an important means of achieving Albania's strategic objectives regarding regional and Euro-Atlantic integration.
Majko was in Washington to attend the annual National Prayer Breakfast.
(ATA - 03/02/04)
